text: Eupterote amaena is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Francis Walker in 1855. It is found on Java and Sumatra.De Heterocera Van Sumatra, Volume 1 The larvae feed on Vitex, Piper, Erythrina and Dioscorea species.The Moths of Borneo ==References== Category:Moths described in 1855 Category:Eupterotinae
title: Eupterote amaena
